cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB 

The paper focuses on comparing citation indexes and their coverage and citation impact, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) is the most likely as it deals with indexing and retrieval of scholarly information. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as it deals with citation analysis and ranking algorithms. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Cryptography (cs.CR) are relevant as they deal with the quality and reliability of data sources. Finally, Databases (cs.DB) is relevant as it deals with indexing and querying large datasets.
